SIMPLE: adamantine
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adamantine
<hw>Ad`a*man"tine</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>adamantinus</ets>, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Made of
adamant, or having the qualities of adamant; incapable of being broken,
dissolved, or penetrated; <as>as, <ex>adamantine</ex> bonds or
chains</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Like the diamond in hardness or
luster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adambulacral</ent>⟦br⟧
